<br />

<br />
I use IE6-SP2, Checkit 86 and Google Toobar and get literally no pop-ups, all being blocked by only IE6-SP2 now. 
<br />

<br />
(Its a fail-safe system. Popups will run through IE6-SP2 blocker, if it somehow gets by it will go through Google Toolbar, and if it gets through THAT, check it 86 will be the last to check it. If it does indeed launch, its adware causing it. And the good thing about it is all these programs use the same hotkey to deactivate popups which is CTRL (hold it and hit refresh or click a link) 
<br />

<br />
Anyway, you might want to check it out from <a href="http://www.microsoft.com/" target="_blank" class="postlink">Microsoft</a>
<br />

<br />
(Note: Windows XP SP2 isnt half bad either, espically for wireless-lan users like myself. And if you don't have a firewall I think Microsoft finally got it right this time, no more McAfee Firewall needed! YAY!) 
<br />

<br />
(Another Note: The Microsoft Internet Explorer Service Pack 2 Popup Blocker is INDEED efficient. Since I installed it, not one popup has gotten through to the Google Toolbar (which means IE is doing it all) and I'm using medium security. )</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
