<tr><td class="printline">
<span class="postbody">I only use IE6 for shockwave and flash content as well as for Windows Update. I find all those long load times annoying as heck. And I have broadband at 3Mb download speed. It is very very rare for me to get popups simply because I use Zone Alarm's popup blocker in addition to the blocker that comes with Mozilla/Firefox. 
<br />

<br />
One tool that I recommend for IE users is Maxthon or MYIE. This has absolutely nothing to do with getting rid of bugs, viruses and adware. It's an add-on to IE that allows for multiple windows on a single iteration of IE. Having multiple windows active in a single iteration of IE consumes less RAM than opening multiple IE's.  Not to mention having less clutter in your task bar. Opening 3 iterations of IE is about the same as using Maxthon with IE. If you're like me you have anywhere from 3-8 windows open at any time.
<br />

<br />
One similar feature also with these add-ons is the ability to open up a set of multiple bookmarks. This means that if you visit the same 5 web sites daily you can have a bookmark of those sites and with the opening of one bookmark you open up all 5 web sites you visit daily (they call them groups in Maxthon, not sure in MYIE). 
<br />

<br />
Tabbed browsing is awesome. Once you start using it, you will definitely hate going back.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
</td></tr>
